    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>
                <addressee>Revd I. Leeser</addressee>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Dear Friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Your<lb/> letters of the <date>5<hi rend="sup">th</hi></date> Ins
                came<lb/> duly to hand, since which<lb/> a box containing<lb/> 2 of the New
                Edition<lb/> of the 40 Bible with the<lb/> parcels pr <persName>Cohen</persName>,<lb/>
                <persName>Jacobs</persName>, <persName>Mois</persName> &amp;
                        <persName>Bradl<add>?</add></persName><lb/> have been safely landed<lb/>
                &amp; all the parcels deli<lb/>vered &amp; forwarded as<lb/> directed.</p>
            <p>You ask for the docu<lb/>ments in relation to the<lb/> debate that took place<lb/>
                between <persName>Dr Raphall</persName><lb/>
                <persName>PB</persName> &amp; <persName>Wise</persName>, <persName>Mr.
                    Levin</persName><lb/> took down the debate<lb/> at the occasion &amp;
                trans<lb/>mitted them to <persName>Dr. R</persName></p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>&amp; which no doubt the<lb/> Dr. has still in his pos<lb/>session &amp; which you
                no<lb/> doubt can obtain upon<lb/> application to him , besides<lb/> this further
                evidence can<lb/> be obtained at <placeName>Albany</placeName><lb/> from the
                Synagogue, or<lb/> the party who opposed<lb/>
                <persName>Wise</persName> return to them after<lb/> he had accepted the<lb/>
                situation of the ministry<lb/> of the <placeName>Haul St </placeName>Synagogue<lb/>
                My affadavit are amongst<lb/> its records in addition<lb/> to others &amp; the whole
                pro<lb/>ceedings as it occurred here<lb/> in that memorable<lb/> debate &amp;
                examination<lb/> but really the Bird is</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>not worth the powder<lb/> &amp; I trust &amp; hope that<lb/> you will treat the<lb/>
                Wise man of the Well<lb/> with contempt &amp; not<lb/> notice him or his
                dia<lb/>bolical remarks. I agree<lb/> with <persName>Dr. R</persName> that it
                can<lb/> not add to your fame<lb/> &amp; is rather derogatory to<lb/> your clerical
                dignity<lb/> to be continually excited<lb/> into a polemic with<lb/> a man of such
                mean<lb/> &amp; contemptible shifts &amp;<lb/>
                <sic>&amp;</sic> perversity. Ere this<lb/> is to hand you have been<lb/> advised of
                    <persName>Revd Mayer</persName><lb/> resignation of his charge<lb/> of the
                    <placeName>Haul St.</placeName> Synagogue<lb/> to take place after the</p>
            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>coming day of atone<lb/>ment, It has long<lb/> been a matter of<lb/>
                <sic>surprize</sic> to us that<lb/> he has not long since<lb/> done what he has
                now<lb/> accomplished, for really<lb/> the contempt &amp; indiffer<lb/>ence with
                which he<lb/> has been treated has<lb/> been such that no<lb/> Revd who had the
                least<lb/> respect for himself &amp;<lb/> his calling ought to have<lb/> submitted
                to such indig<lb/>nity. The congregation<lb/> is dead &amp; reform after<lb/> 20
                years efforts has gone<lb/> as it was predicted.<lb/> What will be the next
                move<lb/> of the Reformers time only will<lb/> dissolve. Your friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">Samuel Hart Sen.</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <placeName>Charleston</placeName>
                <date>Sept 9 1859</date>
            </p>
        </body>
